{"timestamp": "2026-03-20T18:39:28.131375", "elapsed_seconds": 7.037, "stage": "INFO", "message": "Generated response from Gemini", "data": {"response": "To create a simple FastAPI application, follow these steps:\n\n1.  **Create the FastAPI Code**:\n    *   Create an `app` directory and enter it (Document 1).\n    *   Create an empty file named `__init__.py` (Document 1).\n    *   Create a `main.py` file (Document 1).\n\n2.  **Write the Application Code**:\n    In your `main.py` file, you will:\n    *   Import `FastAPI` (Document 1, Document 2).\n    *   Create an `app` instance using `app = FastAPI()` (Document 1, Document 2, Document 9). This `app` variable will be the main point of interaction for your API (Document 9).\n    *   Write a path operation decorator, such as `@app.get(\"/\")` (Document 2).\n    *   Define a path operation function (Document 2).\n\n    An example of the code for `main.py` is:\n    ```python\n    from fastapi import FastAPI\n\n    app = FastAPI()\n\n    @app.get(\"/app\")\n    def read_main():\n        return {\"message\": \"Hello World from main app\"}\n    ```\n    (Document 5)\n\n3.  **Run the Code**:\n    To run your FastAPI application for development, use the `fastapi dev` command (Document 2, Document 3, Document 10):\n    ```bash\n    $ fastapi dev\n    ```\n    (Document 3, Document 10)\n\n    For production, you could use `fastapi run` (Document 4, Document 10).", "response_length": 1230, "tokens_used": 178, "sources_extracted": ["Source: docs\\deployment\\docker.md", "Source: docs\\tutorial\\first-steps.md", "Source: docs\\tutorial\\index.md", "Source: docs\\deployment\\manually.md", "Source: docs\\advanced\\sub-applications.md", "Source: docs\\learn\\index.md", "Source: docs\\deployment\\index.md", "Source: docs\\how-to\\index.md", "Source: docs\\fastapi-cli.md"]}}
